Class FlightManagerMenu

  • java.lang.Object
    • MainPackage.FlightManagerMenu

  • public class FlightManagerMenu
extends java.lang.Object
    A menu that the user can use in order to edit the passenger amount, the selected flight aswell as the passengers seats of a selected flight.
    Author:
    Martin Juul Petersen (mjup@itu.dk), Jesper Nysteen (jnys@itu.dk) and Jonas Kastberg (jkas@itu.dk)

    • Constructor Detail

      • FlightManagerMenu

        public FlightManagerMenu(javax.swing.JFrame frame,
                 Reservation reservation,
                 boolean isNew)
        This class is initialized by passing it a frame to use, since it is not always created with a new JFrame. Since this menu is used in order to create new reserations aswell as editing exsiting ones, we also need to pass it the reservation to use. The boolean passed defines whether the reservation should be uploaded to the database as a new or update an exsisting one.
        Parameters:
        the - frame that everything will be using
        the - reservation to create or edit
        whether - or not the reservation is new or not
